{
  "texts": [
    "This surprise can be quantified mathematically in terms of the variational free energy (F), which is minimized during active inference (i.e., belief updating in the brain):",
    "In the context of this article, free energy provides a mathematical expression for surprise: when the brain is confronted with sensory observations (o) it updates its posterior belief Q s a, about the states of affairs causing those observations.",
    "Note that these states include the states of the world (s) and action upon that world (a).",
    "In the context of a police officer, these could be environmental factors and their behavior.",
    ", given their causes and prior beliefs P s a, about those causes (that include action)."
  ]
}